summary.narrativeincludeclinical:
Initial information received on 30 Sep 2009 via consumer's attorney in form of a civil complain (case # 09 CV 01791): The attorney alleged that the consumer (plaintiff) was infused with Aredia (pamidronate disodium)/Zometa (zoledronate) for an unspecified duration and indication. She then developed osteonecrosis of the jaw. As a result of administration of this drug she suffered physical injury, pain and suffering, emotional distress, mental anguish, infection, physical disability, and physical disfigurement. The patient's status was not specified. No further information was provided.
Follow up information received from a consumer's attorney on 05 Aug 2011 inclusive of medical records. Patient was allergic to amoxicillin. Surgical procedure included incisional biopsy of left breast mass and left modified radical mastectomy. Family history included carcinoma of breast. Records dated 09 May 1994 noted the patient was diagnosed with infiltrating ductal carcinoma and separate nodule of lobular carcinoma in situ. Records of 23 Dec 1999 noted the patient was diagnosed with eczema, chronic low back pain and spondylosis. Records dated 08 Dec 2000 stated the patient had a motor vehicle accident. Patient was a known case of breast cancer metastatis to acetabulum, T12 and L5. The outcome for the events was not reported.
Combined follow-up reports received on 17 Aug 2011 and 22 Aug 2011 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The patient's historical condition and concomitant medications were added. The patient's family history included cancer of pancreas to mother. Record dated 07 Feb 2000 noted hematochezia and internal hemorrhoids in patient. The patient underwent tonsillectiomy on an unspecified date. As per the record, the patient was started monthly dose of Aredia 90 mg intravenously on 24 Jan 2000. The record dated 24 Jan 2000 stated that the patient had cystitis. Record dated 15 Aug 2001 stated that the patient had liver and right renal cyst and flank pain. Record dated 15 Mar 2007 reported that the patient was smoker. Records dated 11 Dec 2007 noted that the patient suffered right eye swelling. Records dated 06 Mar 2008 stated that the patient had diverticulosis. The record dated 10 Jul 2008 stated that the patient had hypermetabolism and multiple osseous metastases. The record dated 06 Aug 2008; the patient received Aredia 30 mg on an unspecified date (three weeks ago) and developed allergic reaction around the eyes. The patient had gastric reflux. As per the record dated 28 Aug 2008, the Aredia was discontinued. The record dated 30 Oct 2008 indicated that the patient suffered metastases to both lungs. As per the record dated 23 Jan 2009 the patient developed cellulitis and received treatment with Keflex (cefalexin). The record dated 24 Apr 2009 stated that the patient was allergic to bisphosphonates, Singulair (montelukast), latex, Aredia and erythromycin. The record dated 10 Jul 2009 stated that the patient developed thrush and received nystatin for treatment. The record dated 07 Oct 2009 noted nasal ulceration and patient received treatment with clindamycin. Records dated 11 Nov 2009 reported shingles to patient. The patient was reported as recovering from the event 'shingles'. Records dated 19 Apr 2010 stated that the patient experienced bone pain, osteolytic lesion, osteoporosis and anemia secondary to chemotherapy. Record dated 03 Nov 2010 stated that the patient suffered essential hypertension. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up information received from a consumer's attorney on 26 Aug 2011 inclusive of medical records. The record dated 10 Jan 2008 stated that the patient had coronary artery disease. The receord dated 18 Jan 2008 stated that the patient experienced right hip and leg pain. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney on 07 Sep 2011 inclusive of medical records: History and concomitant medications updated. Records dated 08 Apr 2003 noted that the patient experienced recurrent sinusitis. Treatment with Levaquin (levofloxacin) 500 mg q.d was started. On 07 Jul 2005, noted that the patient developed severe dyshidrotic eczema. She also reported having heartburn and urticaria. Records dated 22 Jun 2006 noted that the patient was diagnosed with colon polyp and degenerative joint disease. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Combined follow-up reports received from the consumer's attorney on 27 Sep 2011 and 30 Sep 2011 inclusive of medical records: Records dated 26 Jul 2005 stated that the patient had asthma and depression. On 13 Dec 2007, MRI revealed meningitis. Records dated 08 Jan 2008 noted that the patient had right sided orbital cellulitis. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up received on 14 Oct 2011 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The patient's concomitant medications were updated. The medical record dated 11 Dec 2007 stated that the patient had chest pain, right eye lid erythma, viral conjunctivitis, eye pain, eye floaters, hay fever and migraine headaches. On 12 Dec 2007 the patient diagnosed with periorbital cellulitis and she was therefore admitted to the hospital for intravenous (IV) antibiotics and patient was improving with IV antibiotics. It was also reported that her skin was extremely inflamed on admission, especially in the extremities and she was started on topical Temovate (clobetasol) ointment, applied this a couple times and had improvement. On 16 Dec 2007 the patient was discharged. The record dated 18 Dec 2007 stated that the outcome of the events were worsening for periorbital swelling, tenderness around the right eye and condition improving for periorbital cellulitis. The outcome of the rest of events was not reported.
Follow-up received on 19 Oct 2011 from a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Patient's history and concomitant medications were updated. Records dated 24 Jul 2007 noted GI upset, pain near ears and facial pain. Records dated 25 Jul 2007 noted myofascial pain. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Combined follow up received on 02 Nov 2011 and 03 Nov 2011 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Surgical history of the patient included C-section. Family history included sinus problems, nasal allergies, nasal polyps. Records dated 14 Apr 2003 noted the patient had nasal vestibulitis and chronic ethmoid and maxillary sinusitis. Records dated 20 Feb 2008 noted that the patient's sleep was disturbed. The outcome for the events was not reported.
Follow up received on 09 Nov 2011, via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: The patient started on Aredia for bone strengthening or cancer treatment. The records dated 24 Aug 2008, stated that the patient developed facial swelling. The final outcome of the event was not reported.
Follow-up report received from the consumer's attorney on 30 Nov 2011 inclusive of medical records: The patient had a medical history of flu, Tinea corporis and appendectomy. Current condition included severe hand dermatitis. Records dated 13 Aug 2004 noted that the patient was diagnosed with a mucosal gumline infection and angioedema of face. She also had a left hip fracture. The outcome of the events was provided.
Follow-up received on 03 Jan 2012 from a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. The patient was allergic to codeine. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up received on 05 Jun 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Records dated 22 Feb 2012 stated that the patient had neuropathy. Records dated 09 May 2012 stated that the patient developed metastases to the liver as well as lymph nodes. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up received on 18 Jul 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records: Record dated 06 Apr 2011 noted that patient was suffering from cortical senile cataract. The outcome of the event was not reported.
Follow-up received on 22 Oct 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Patient's current condition included secondary malignant neoplasm breast. Patient's historical condition included vesicles. Record dated 10 Jan 2002 stated that the patient had Paget's disease. Record dated 21 Feb 2007 stated that the patient had blepharochalasis of the upper lids and hyperopia. Record dated 08 Oct 2008 stated that the patient had astigmatism and presbyopia. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow-up received on 23 Oct 2012 via consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. MRI dated 09 Aug 2012 stated that the patient had arthropathy in the left hip joint and some soft tissue calcification. MRI dated 13 Aug 2012 stated that the patient had deformity of the left hip. The outcome of the events was not reported.
Follow up received on 06 Dec 2012 via a consumer's attorney inclusive of medical records. Record dated 19 Apr 2010 noted that patient was suffering from skin inflammation and desquamation. Record dated 23 Feb 2011 noted that patient was suffering from leukopenia. Record dated 16 Jun 2012 noted that patient had received radiation therapy to hands and feet. Patient was also suffering from pleural thickening. Record dated 16 Aug 2012 noted that patient suffered from chronic bone erosion of the left femoral head. Record dated 03 Oct 2012 noted that patient suffered from skin lesion. Record dated 31 Oct 2012 noted that patient suffered from atrophy in the left hip joint. Record dated 14 Nov 2012 noted that patient suffered from bursitis. The outcome of the events was not reported.
summary.sendercomment: MAC: Review of available data reported in this legal case does not allow for proper causality assessments. Some conditions found in the report may not have developed under treatment with the product, as some events are not dated and it is not clearly reported when treatment with Zometa stopped.
